Online auctions for accident cars
In October, the Solera Group purchased Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles that were damaged.
The operation involved a cost of <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>59.5 million for 85% of the company’s capital, which could expand next year to the remaining 15%.
The aim of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of accessing a huge international market.
This estimate and sales service is intended exclusively for industry professionals, such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, garages, cash registers and professional sellers who must be registered before they begin to carry out operations.
Established in 1996 in Germany, this platform manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, including 500,000 in Germany.
Among its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1,500 sellers and 4,000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3,000 ads per day and in the Spanish market, 100 new ads are published every day.
